{"id": 223701862, "title": "In Pictures: Competitors all revved up for lawnmower racing world champs", "text": "Competitors have descended on Surrey to take part in the World Lawnmower Championships. The event is being held by the British Lawn Mower Racing Association (BLMRA) at Pondfield Farm, Alford. The association says lawn mower racing started in 1973 when an Irishman named Jim Gavin was looking for a cheaper form of motorsport. The main objectives were \u2013 and still are \u2013 no sponsorship, no commercialism, no cash prizes and no modifying of engines. With the aim of keeping costs down, the resulting race series has been described by Motor Sport News as \u201cthe cheapest form of motorsport in the UK\u201d. The BLMRA still sticks to its origins as a non-profit making organisation, with any money generated given to good causes.", "summary": "The BLMRA still sticks to its origins as a non-profit making organisation, with any money generated given to good causes.", "url": "https://www.standard.co.uk/news/uk/andrew-matthews-surrey-british-b1160316.html", "image": "https://static.standard.co.uk/2024/05/26/14/5788d7ef6d7af25699ab69d3c8c5193dY29udGVudHNlYXJjaGFwaSwxNzE2ODE0MTg5-2.76336434.jpg?width=1200", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 13:27:48", "author": null, "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.549}